Two men were seriously injured after the plane they were in crashed on the R44 between Stellenbosch and Strand in Cape Town. Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911â€™s spokesperson, said the incident happened just after 11.30 am on Wednesday. He said reports indicate that a Piper PA-28 Cherokee light aircraft had made a forced landing on the main road. Herbst said the pilot and passenger suffered serious injuries. They were both taken to hospital. He said circumstances leading up to the incident will be investigated by the relevant authorities.